{
  "stem": "26142.13",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that's the way the upbringing that I had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was inside of me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I couldn't, I couldn't break, I couldn't break it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And but I, I managed to come back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the next 24 hours, straight, straight to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that brings us to sometimes in October of 1943.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We stayed there for another month at that work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in October, '43-- in November, rather-- they packed us up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we never knew where they're, where they're shipping us, where we are going.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The military, you don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They put us on trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all we saw that we are traveling to the-- again to the Carpathian, to the, to the-- they are shipping us out to the front where the war is going on.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we stopped in, in-- for some reason, I don't know what the reason is-- we stopped in December.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "December 1, we stopped in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we didn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were taken off the trains and, and, and settled in in a place there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All we did was they would march us out every day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Why they, they didn't ship us straight out into, into the war front, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I think, I think at that winter of between '43 and '44, that was the winter when the Russians broke through the front in [INAUDIBLE] And [INAUDIBLE] was, was the line that the Hungarian military were holding.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they had a tremendous defeat in, in, in that, that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So either that wasn't enough, enough rails-- I mean cars-- available, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we stayed on for four weeks, almost to the end in December, almost to the end of December.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In December, we finally got shipped out again into the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where are we now?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
